    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1142"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1142">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spring Rice</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Acting Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Excellency the
                    British Ambassador and has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of his
                    memorandum of August 29, 1914, in which he suggests that the presence of an
                    American war vessel in Liberian waters is necessary to enable the Government of
                    Liberia to discharge its obligations as a neutral.</p>
                <p>In reply the British Embassy is advised that the suggestion made in its
                    memorandum is receiving the Department’s consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,</closer>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-08">
                        <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
